<hr>

<p><b>
<img align=left src="../images/ohiocoatings-blue.jpg" width=127 height=93
  hspace=10 alt="Ohio Coatings Company">
Wheeling-Pittsburgh holds a 50 percent interest in the Ohio Coatings Company
joint venture.  The other partners include Dong Yang Tinplate Limited,
South Korea, and Nittetsu Shoji America, Los Angeles.  Ohio Coatings,
located in Yorkville, Ohio, will produce electrolytically tinplated steel
once construction of the company's plant is completed in late 1996.
Wheeling-Pittsburgh will serve as the primary steel supplier to the new
facility.
</b></p>

<hr>

<table>
<tr valign=top>
 <td><img width=250 height=183 hspace=10 
  src="../images/nisshin-jointventure.jpg" alt="Wheeling-Nisshin, Inc."></td>
 <td><b>
Wheeling-Pittsburgh Steel owns a 36 percent interest in Wheeling-Nisshin,
Inc., Follansbee, West Virginia.  The remaining ownership interest is
held by
Nisshin Steel Company, Limited, Japan.  Wheeling-Nisshin manufactures
hot dipped galvanized, galvalume, galvannealed and aluminized products.
Wheeling-Pittsburgh is the major steel supplier to this joint venture.
</b></td>
</tr>
</table>

<hr>

<table>
<tr valign=top>
 <td><b>
Another joint venture includes Wheeling-Pittsburgh and ISPAT Mexicana, SA
DeC.V., Mexico.  The joint venture purchases steel slabs from ISPAT's IMEXA
plant in Mexico.  The slabs are converted, for the joint venture, into hot
rolled steel coils at Wheeling-Pittsburgh's 80-Inch Hot Strip Mill, utilizing
Wheeling-Pittsburgh's otherwise excess rolling capacity.  Wheeling-Pittsburgh
markets the coils under the agreement.  Both companies hold equal ownership
in the joint venture.
</b></td>
 <td><img width=250 height=183 hspace=10 
   src="../images/ispat-jointventure.jpg" alt="ISPAT Mexicana"></td>
</tr>
</table>
 

